A (\text{adj} A) = (\det A) I
\det((A) (\text{adj} A))= \det((\det A) I) \text{ or } (\det A) (\det(\text{adj} A)) = (\det A)^n
\det((\det A) I)
(\det A)^n
det(A)I
det(A)
A = c I
c
\det A = \sum_\sigma \operatorname{ sgn} \sigma [A]_{1,\sigma_1} \cdots \sigma [A]_{n,\sigma_n}
[A]_{ij} = c \delta_{ij}
\det A = c^n\sum_\sigma \operatorname{ sgn} \sigma \delta_{1,\sigma_1} \cdots \delta_{n,\sigma_n}
\delta_{1,\sigma_1} \cdots \delta_{n,\sigma_n} = \begin{cases} 1, & \text{if } \sigma_k = k \ \forall k \\ 0, & \text{otherwise}\end{cases}
\det A = c^n
